{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Problem\nMigrate the code_health size metrics off the hardcoded `src/rebar` scan + `.github/module-size-limit.txt` onto the analyzer + `[code_health]` config, so a non-Python client gets honest Unavailable instead of fabricated zeros. Does NOT touch the CI module-size GATE (separate governance).\n\n## Mechanism (G6 — grounded in the existing registry adapter; positive rationale)\nThe registry wires metrics via a single-arg context adapter: `_spec(id, fn, ranged)` builds a MetricSpec whose `compute(ctx)` reads `ctx.repo_root` (+`since`/`until`) and calls `fn(...)` (git_metrics.py registry-integration region). Chosen approach (mirrors that pattern — codebase-aligned, minimal, keeps analyzer resolution in one place):\n1. Add an ANALYZER context adapter `_analyzer_spec(id, fn)`: its `compute(ctx)` calls `resolve_analyzer(lang)` from `[rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]` (which returns None when no analyzer is configured), runs it over `ctx.repo_root` + `ctx.scan_roots`, obtaining an `AnalyzerResult [rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`; then calls `fn(analyzer_result.loc, ctx.size_cap, ctx.size_near_fraction)`. If `resolve_analyzer` returns None, or the result is `Unavailable`, `compute` returns `None` (-> the registry renders Unavailable). Alternatives considered (fn resolves its own analyzer; a new ctx field carrying a pre-resolved result) are rejected: keeping resolution in the adapter matches `_spec` and avoids duplicating resolution across fns.\n2. Wire config onto ctx: `_commands/metrics.py` (which today builds `ctx = SimpleNamespace(repo_root, since, until)`) is extended to also set `scan_roots`, `analyzers`, `size_cap`, `size_near_fraction` read from the `[code_health]` config section `[rebar:e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb]`.\n3. Rework the fns to read the scc adapter's LOC payload (shape defined by `[rebar:18f9-5b75-b909-408c]`: `loc = {\"files\": {path:int}, \"max_loc\": int}`):\n   - `module_size_distribution(loc, size_cap, size_near_fraction) -> {\"count\",\"near_cap_count\",\"over_cap_count\",\"max_loc\"}`: count=len(loc[\"files\"]); over_cap_count=#files>size_cap; near_cap_count=#files in [size_cap*(1-size_near_fraction), size_cap]; max_loc=loc[\"max_loc\"].\n   - `oversized_module_count(loc, size_cap) -> int` (#files>size_cap) — today a `_no_data_yet` seed stub; gains this real compute.\n4. Remove `_LIMIT_FILE`/`_read_cap`/the `src/rebar` rglob. DEREGISTER `cap_change_events` (rebar-governance artifact, no client analogue) from `register()`. `module_size_trend` stays a seed stub returning **Unavailable**: a scc-based snapshot WRITER to feed a trend series does not exist and is OUT OF SCOPE / deferred to a follow-up.\n5. PROVENANCE (T8): the analyzer-derived `module_size_distribution` / `oversized_module_count` MetricSpec entries carry `source=\"structural\"` (analyzer measurement, not a git derivation), `lens=\"code_health\"`.\n\n## Grounding (E4 — verified via Read)\n- CONFIRMED git_metrics.py `_LIMIT_FILE`:35, `_read_cap`:75, `src/rebar` rglob :93, `cap_change_events`:167 registered ~:272; `_spec`/`register` in the registry-integration region (compute(ctx) reads ctx.repo_root/since/until, calls fn).\n- CONFIRMED `_commands/metrics.py` builds `ctx = SimpleNamespace(repo_root, since, until)` (extended here to carry the [code_health] config).\n- Contracts: `AnalyzerResult`/`resolve_analyzer`/`Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` `[rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`; loc payload shape `{\"files\":{path:int},\"max_loc\":int}` `[rebar:18f9-5b75-b909-408c]`; config keys `size_cap:int|None`/`size_near_fraction:float`/`scan_roots:list[str]`/`analyzers:dict[str,str]` `[rebar:e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb]` (all depends_on edges recorded).\n- OLD-behavior tests to update: `tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py`, `tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py`.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command)\n- [ ] No metric reader references the old hardcodes. PROVE: `! grep -Eq \"src/rebar|module-size-limit.txt\" src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`.\n- [ ] Configured positive path: a synthetic AnalyzerResult with `loc={\"files\":{\"a\":100,\"b\":850},\"max_loc\":850}`, size_cap=800 -> module_size_distribution returns count==2, over_cap_count==1, max_loc==850; oversized_module_count==1. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_configured_positive`.\n- [ ] the analyzer-derived specs carry `source=\"structural\"`. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_provenance`.\n- [ ] `cap_change_events` no longer registered. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py::test_cap_change_events_deregistered`.\n- [ ] `module_size_trend` returns Unavailable (no writer). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py::test_trend_unavailable`.\n- [ ] Unconfigured analyzer (resolve_analyzer -> None) -> Unavailable, NOT `{count:0,max_loc:0}` authoritative, no leaked errno. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py::test_foreign_repo_honest_unavailable`.\n- [ ] churn / refactor_to_addition_ratio + agent_process metrics unchanged; updated git_metrics tests green. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py`.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 18f9, 21fb, 3ba0, e7a0 (recorded depends_on).\n## Files likely touched\n- src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py (add `_analyzer_spec` + reworked fns; remove hardcodes + `cap_change_events`)\n- src/rebar/metrics/registry.py (seed-spec adjustments for module_size_trend / oversized_module_count)\n- src/rebar/_commands/metrics.py (ctx carries the [code_health] config)\n- tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics.py, tests/unit/metrics/test_git_metrics_heldout.py, tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py\n## Estimated scope: M-L"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784609242509540001,"uuid":"8e49ea5f-36de-47f1-bd9f-06d754b8df62"}